                                         JOHANNESBURG - The City of Johannesburg says there is no place for drug dens in the metro. This comes after a crime prevention operation at two properties in Zuurfontein, south of the city, where several crystal meth pipes were seized. City spokesperson Lucky Sindane says management is cleaning up the city to ensure a prosperous and inclusive place for resident. “We also seized 12 cases of alcohol and issued a fine to the seller, who was trading without a licence. We also fined another owner for not registering a second-hand goods shop.”  (Edited by Shimoney Regter)